<div class="main-complaint-container complaint-div card-good-own">

  
  <div class="card complaint-div" style="width: 30rem;">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Privacy Policy for College Buzz</h5><br>
    <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-2 text-body-secondary">Complete Policy Statement</h6><br>
    <p class="card-text">College Buzz is a student oriented platform created to bring together communication, event updates, academic resources and campus buzz in one place. We respect your privacy and this document explains in detail how we collect, use, protect and manage your information. When you use College Buzz you may provide personal details such as your name, email address, phone number, roll number, profile photo and academic information including courses, assignments and grades. We also store community interactions such as posts, comments, likes and group discussions. Technical information like IP address, browser type, operating system and device identifiers is automatically collected. If you enable location services we may record approximate GPS or IP based location. Usage analytics such as login frequency, time spent and features accessed are saved in our system. Optional inputs such as feedback forms, surveys, polls and event registrations are also stored in our database. We use your information primarily to operate and improve the service. Data is processed to provide personalized content and recommendations. Communication between students, faculty and administrators is simplified through the use of your information. Notifications, alerts and event reminders are sent using the details you provide. Security and fraud prevention are supported by monitoring and verification. Research and analytics are conducted on anonymized data to make the platform better. We never sell your personal data. Limited sharing may occur with third party vendors for hosting, analytics, payment gateways and technical support. Data may be disclosed if required by law or court order. Information may also be shared if necessary to protect the safety of users or the integrity of the platform. Data is stored on encrypted servers with SSL encryption, firewalls and secure authentication. Only authorized personnel can access the information. Regular security audits and vulnerability checks are performed. However no system is completely secure and users are advised to keep their passwords strong and confidential. Cookies are used to remember login sessions and preferences. Analytics cookies help us understand user behavior. Users can disable cookies in their browser settings but some features may not function properly. Users have rights over their data including the ability to access stored information, correct inaccurate details, delete accounts and remove data, restrict processing and export their data. College Buzz is designed for college students and we do not knowingly collect data from individuals under the age of thirteen. If such data is discovered it will be deleted immediately. The platform may contain links to external websites and we are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites. We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time and major changes will be communicated through email or app notifications. If you have any questions or concerns you can contact us by email at support@collegebuzz.edu, by phone at +911789545789, or by visiting our office at Nit Raipur ACE. By using College Buzz you agree that your data will be collected and processed according to this Privacy Policy.</p>
</div>
